					<h1>Marketing Cohorts</h1>
					<p>When starting a new campaign, you may have experienced the thrill of the situation, when your campaign managed to hit and introduce thousands of users in the early stages of your sales funnel, but you are still uncertain how many will hit the end of the funnel where they are supposed to actually pay.</p>
					<p>In these cases it may be useful to track the performances of your campaigns and to track whether your users are behaving as you expect. In the case shown below our client was tracking  how many free SIM Cards sent on demand were activated weeks after the delivery.</p>
					<p>As you can see (image on the right), roughly 70% of all activations were made 3 weeks after the start of the campaign making a ratio of approx. 30% of all the cards sent.</p>
