				<div class="desc">
					<h1>Marketing Cohorts</h1>
					<p>Betting on one single marketing type may be tricky. Typically you may have experienced that incomes from commercial mailing lists may wither away as reclamations or failed payments or otherwise unfinished transactions may increase over time. On the other hand other not so much apparent sources with greater brand impact may give you significant  incomes over time that may go unnoticed from a short perspective.</p>
					<p>In the graph on the right you may notice that the very first marketing campaign made by our client in january 2013 made nowadays 20% of his total income.</p>
					<p>Tracking such incomes in context with other expenditures as such as support and other overhead costs may be very rewarding when looking for sustainable business models.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</article>

		{# CUSTOMER BEHAVIOR #}

