				<div class="desc">
					<h1>Customer behaviour</h1>

					<p>It probably happened to all of us more than once - you expected your customer to behave in a certain way only to learn afterwards that the reality was different.</p>
					<p>Our client was relying on a vast and quite expensive network of partner organisations in order to allow his own customers to pay for its services. When looking to the payment distribution chart he realised that 95% percents of orders were made by channels requiring roughly 60 % of the expenses. By cutting the unneeded partners he managed afterwards to significantly improve the overall profitability of his service.</p>
				</div>
